  "text": "Equalization is a powerful technique to compensate such multipath fading problems. Two types of equalization methods are used according to their purposes as training-aided equalization method and blind method. In wireless sensor networks in which sensors usually work with low duty-cycle training-aided equalizers need a sufficiently long training sequence in each data packet [CITATION_1] . The training-aided equalizer algorithms are not suitable since equalizers for wireless sensor networks require the function of mitigation of multipath propagation and the efficiency of bandwidth, energy and cost as well [CITATION_2] .",
